# =============================================================================
# Whitelist .gitignore for the Tomo Digital take-home.
#
# Strategy: ignore everything by default, then re-allow only the files this
# exercise actually owns:
#   - wp-content/plugins/agency-client-plugin/  (the plugin we work on)
#   - docs/                                     (our answers)
#   - tools/, bin/                              (helpers shipped with the repo)
#   - docker-compose.yml, README.md, .gitignore
#
# WordPress core, themes, other plugins, wp-config.php, and the SQLite database
# are NOT tracked. Local environment values (e.g. ACP_AUTHORITY_API) live in
# wp-config.php and are documented in docs/SETUP.md so a teammate can reproduce.
# =============================================================================

# Ignore everything by default.
*

# --- Repo metadata ----------------------------------------------------------
!.gitignore
!.gitattributes
!README.md
!docker-compose.yml

# --- Our docs ---------------------------------------------------------------
!docs/
!docs/**

# --- Mock API + seed helpers shipped with the exercise ----------------------
!tools/
!tools/**
!bin/
!bin/**

# --- Path to the plugin we own ----------------------------------------------
# Re-allow each path segment, then ignore siblings inside each segment so we
# don't accidentally pull in WP core / akismet / themes.
!wp-content/
wp-content/*
!wp-content/plugins/
wp-content/plugins/*
!wp-content/plugins/agency-client-plugin/
!wp-content/plugins/agency-client-plugin/**

# --- Junk that should never be committed even inside whitelisted folders ----
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.log
*.swp
*~
*.bak
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
.idea/
.vscode/
node_modules/
vendor/
